{"compliance_id": "71aaa20d-d71a-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "document_type": "Monitoring Returns", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/LicenseeReturns/byid?lr_id=71aaa20d-d71a-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "title": "Annual 2024 Noise Monitoring Report", "description": "Annual 2024 Noise Monitoring Report + Fehily & Timoneys report for 1st and 2nd round of noise monitoring for 2024.

For round 1 (day), noise levels were above ELV of 55dB for all monitoring locations. The highest levels were measured off-site, with frequent road traffic and off-site commercial activities the main contributing factor to elevated levels. On-site exceedance was partially due to significant site activity, i.e on-site vehicle movement entering/ tipping on site & also leaving site.

For round 2 (night), noise levels were below ELV of 45dB for four monitoring locations. Noise levels were above the limit for three locations. The locations where exceedances were measured are monitoring locations on the Greenhill's road. The report concludes that frequent road traffic noise was the main noise contributing factor.", "submission_date": "", "status": "Closed", "metadata": "{"licenseereturnid": "71aaa20d-d71a-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a", "type": "Monitoring Returns", "reference": "LR093675", "subject": "Monitoring Returns:Noise", "status": "Closed", "licenceid": "4ac9e87d-7c61-e211-9eb5-0050568a69e2", "licenceprofileid": "f5652da1-291c-4422-92d9-50a15b21fe02", "datereceived": "2025-04-16T00:00:00", "closeddate": "2025-05-02T00:00:00", "title": "Annual 2024 Noise Monitoring Report", "doctype": "Monitoring Returns", "docsubtype": "Noise", "decision": "Assessed", "description": "Annual 2024 Noise Monitoring Report + Fehily & Timoneys report for 1st and 2nd round of noise monitoring for 2024.\r\n\r\nFor round 1 (day), noise levels were above ELV of 55dB for all monitoring locations. The highest levels were measured off-site, with frequent road traffic and off-site commercial activities the main contributing factor to elevated levels. On-site exceedance was partially due to significant site activity, i.e on-site vehicle movement entering/ tipping on site & also leaving site.\r\n\r\nFor round 2 (night), noise levels were below ELV of 45dB for four monitoring locations. Noise levels were above the limit for three locations. The locations where exceedances were measured are monitoring locations on the Greenhill's road. The report concludes that frequent road traffic noise was the main noise contributing factor.", "documentcategory": "Non-Compliant", "complianceinvestigationid": null}"}

